The United States strongly condemns a terrorist attack carried out by a Pakistan-based group that killed over 40 Indian paramilitary forces and injured at least 44 others. The US expresses condolences to the victims' families, the Indian government, and the Indian people. The US is calling on Pakistan to immediately stop supporting and providing safe haven to all terrorist groups operating within its borders. The attack has reinforced the US's determination to enhance counterterrorism cooperation between the US and India.